1.title: Europe or Bust
1.plot: In the Season 4 premiere, a politician mixes work life and family life; three mountain bikers need an RV that'll get them to Colorado's most rugged trails; and two adventurous full-timers want a downsized RV for their European holiday.

2.title: Home on the Road
2.plot: Three lifelong friends who call themselves the "Divas Do" want an RV for a cross-country road trip.

3.title: Rocky Mountain High
3.plot: Old friends shop for an RV for a cross-country mother-daughter trip; a couple search for a luxury coach that's bearproof; and two polar explorers need a mountain-ready ride.

4.title: Brocation
4.plot: Best friends look for the ultimate party mobile in Tampa. In Tucson, a mountain-biking family have $85,000 to spend on an RV that'll let them go anywhere.

5.plot: A minister and his wife are tempted on a tour of travel trailers; a singing Sheriff and his bluegrass pickin' wife have a showdown over the perfect RV; and a showbiz family want to kick things up a notch.

6.title: Just for the Halibut
6.plot: Tampa rock-and-roll trio Acting Natural dream of going national, but before they hit the road they're going to need a better ride. Then, a Denver family want an RV for fishing trips, but their tight budget makes finding the perfect camper a tall order. Finally, college sweethearts who are football fanatics want an RV so they can follow their favorite team all season, but they need plenty of room for their two huge dogs.

7.title: Game On
7.plot: A volleyball team need to score an RV for out-of-town games; a couple and their dog need a posh coach for a family vacation; and an adoptive couple want an RV to take their new daughters on a tour of the country.

8.title: Land Yachts and Pop Ups
8.plot: The Escape the Room team want to go mobile and are on the hunt for a fifth wheel with nooks and crannies for clues, plus a surprise or two for guests. In Tampa, two boaters want to drop anchor and hit some landlocked locations in a luxury land yacht. In Denver, two exes-turned-best friends hope to remain close in a tiny trailer they can take on the road and share their mutual love of adventures, festivals and fun.

10.plot: Buyers with one-of-a-kind personalities search for the perfect RV.

4.plot: Newlyweds upgrade to a pop-up camper; the perfect home away from home; entrepreneurs sell everything to live the RV lifestyle.

5.plot: A fifth wheel trailer for parents with a grand kitchen and a bathroom fit for royalty; a motorcycle family needs more horsepower.

6.plot: A shiny toy hauler for a biker couple; a motor home picked by a show dog; a traveling hair salon for a stylist.

7.plot: Cowboy searches for RV to fit his traveling rodeo lifestyle but struggles to find comfortable living space; hippies trade in their shagging wagon for modern amenities; young family wants ample storage space for their weekend toys.

8.plot: Family's search for a big RV conflicts with mom's ability to get comfortable behind the wheel; rugby team wants a massive bathroom and outdoor entertaining space; beekeeper needs a comfortable trailer to take her bees on the road.

9.plot: Traveling circus of 3 upgrades from yellow school bus to spacious coach; parents need extra sleeping space for fishing adventures; entrepreneurs need extra tow capacity to take their commercial auction business cross country.

10.plot: A family of five sees stars over a high-end RV fit for a rock star; best friends and party girls hit a few bumps to make it to the Kentucky Derby; and a couple shops for a 5th wheel to house their custom golf carts.

11.plot: Couple faces the possibility of a completely rotted floor; entrepreneurs sell their house to buy a luxury coach to live their dream & travel to all 50 states; rock-climbing business wants flashy RV to shuttle clients on excursions

12.title: The Best for the Beasts
12.plot: International horse trainer needs a mobile stable that doubles as her second home; business owners sell off their Wi-Fi Internet company to cash in on the RV lifestyle; a retired couple treats themselves to a luxury upgrade.

13.title: Absolute Lap of Luxury
13.plot: A couple shop for a compact and luxurious RV suitable for their toddler; a family are determined to go home with a trailer that sleeps six comfortably; and online instructors have their dogs and enough room to do yoga to consider when making a purchase.

14.plot: A 42-foot RV is the envy of other tailgate enthusiasts prior to a Tampa Bay Buccaneers game; a newly engaged couple struggle to compromise on size; and an equestrian family are in need of an upgrade.

1.plot: In the Season 3 premiere, two artists want a masterpiece; and an Elvis impersonator needs a King RV.

2.title: Triple Trade-In
2.plot: RV bloggers search for a new ride; demolition derby promoters need an upgrade; and a family of five want closeness on the road.

3.title: A Song for the Ride
3.plot: A retro singing trio require a classic touring RV; a Navy vet and his family are looking to create some lifelong memories; and two design divas plan to glam up the nation in a luxury ride.

4.title: Daredevils and Dirt Bikes
4.plot: A professional dirt bike racer and his wife need to upgrade their full-time RV while balancing a growing brood with room for bikes; a circus troupe family require a road warrior; and a retired couple with a lap dog search for luxury.

5.title: Bombshells Away
5.plot: An a cappella group want to travel from gig to gig like rock stars; makeup artists search for a budget-friendly RV; and a family with college-bound triplets look for an upgrade that won't deplete their tuition fund.

6.plot: A couple search for the ultimate tailgating base; a model and her BFFS decide that an RV would be fun; and a family with two babies and two motorbikes want to trade in and trade up.

7.title: Country Cool
7.plot: Two country divas need an RV good enough for the biggest celebrities; a pro wrestler is looking for a vehicle to kick back in after kicking butt; and a family of five try to reach an agreement on their big purchase.

8.title: Princesses and Pigs
8.plot: Well-heeled parents-to-be search for a coach with room to grow and ultramodern luxury; a pageant family need a rolling green room with style; and a young couple hunt for their first RV for a family camping adventure.

9.title: Two for the Road
9.plot: High rollers look to add an RV with flash to their fleet; a traveling magician wants to house his entire family in style; and a young couple try to strike the right balance between bare bones and comfort when purchasing their first family camper.

10.title: Surfing Safari
10.plot: A surfing family search for a rad RV for their cross-country trip out west; a firefighter and his wife hope to find a decked-out coach for their many camping excursions; and a couple of full-time RVers look to upsize.

11.title: A Sweet Ride
11.plot: Different height requirements go into the purchase of an RV for a big family road trip. Also: The perfect rolling bakery is sought for a cookie business; and a retired couple decide to rough it...in luxury.

12.title: Honeymoon Suite
12.plot: Two cyclists buddies shop for an RV for expeditions; adventurous newlyweds are in the market for a honeymoon love nest; and a family of six are hoping to find a spacious recreational vehicle for a lifetime of memories.

13.title: Doggone Ride
13.plot: A dog rescue group look for an RV that will keep their canines comfy; two adventure lovers decide it's time to upgrade to some serious luxury; and a father wants to spend more time outdoors with his family.
